But I mean I think all great
authors critique the moments

00:49:20.260 --> 00:49:21.560
that they live in right.

00:49:21.560 --> 00:49:24.600
I have a hard time thinking of
any author who doesn't right,

00:49:24.600 --> 00:49:26.090
whose work we still read today.

00:49:26.090 --> 00:49:30.230
I mean Voltaire does the same
thing for France, you know,

00:49:30.230 --> 00:49:34.560 position:56%
has a similar quest narrative there.

00:49:34.560 --> 00:49:39.710
So I think that we can paint with a
broad brush in saying that there's

00:49:39.710 --> 00:49:42.970
that sense of disenchantment, but
I agree that it's good to look

00:49:42.970 --> 00:49:48.460
at their specific historical
consequences and circumstances.

00:49:48.460 --> 00:49:52.540
So do you want to -- do you have an
